## Why this works

`RecipeHelper.safeGetRecipesFor` returns a fresh authoritative list from the current matrix. If the matrix is empty or has mismatched ingredients, the list is empty and `resultIndex >= fresh.size()` short-circuits before any item is placed in the result slot. The method no longer reads from potentially-stale `matchedCraftingRecipes`.

## Regression risk

- Legit multi-result recipe selection still works: the fresh list is identical to what the client just saw when the result lists were populated legitimately (inputs unchanged in the ~1 tick round-trip).
- `craftResult.method_7665` continues to fire, preserving "recipe used" tracking.
- No change to the `method_7667` (take) handler — input consumption there is already correct when inputs are present.
